Whitefish: 0.089 ppm
Herring: 0.084 ppm
Hake: 0.079 ppm                         <- supposed to have health benefits 
Trout: 0.071 ppm
Crab: 0.065 ppm
Haddock: 0.055 ppm
Whiting: 0.051 ppm
Atlantic mackerel: 0.050 ppm
Crayfish: 0.035 ppm
Pollock: 0.031 ppm
Catfish: 0.025 ppm
Squid: 0.023 ppm                        <- eat more 
Salmon: 0.022 ppm                       <- staple 
Anchovies: 0.017 ppm                    <- also supposed to have health benefits
Sardines: 0.013 ppm
Oysters: 0.012 ppm                      <- worth mentioning 
Scallops: 0.003 ppm
Shrimp: 0.001 ppm


Regularly eating fish with mercury concentrations greater than 0.3 ppm (parts per million) may increase the risk of health issues. 
  The FDA has set a limit of 1 ppm for methylmercury in fish for human consumption. 
  dice seem to feel 0.26 is the upper limit 




